up spells</span><hr size=1>   Would be a really nice little hitch of Verant to add in the ability for certain casters to cast spells together.  Maybe a timing issue where if they both land within a certain time of one another you get added effect, or for ease of programming, make the first half of the spell be sort of a buff, which achieves only allowing the other person to cast their spell off for insanely cool looking, and possibly even effective, spells.<br>
<br>
  An example I can think of would be Wizz_1 and Druid_1 group up.<br>
<br>
  They find Helpless_1 wandering by, and seeing that it is a red con, team up on it's poor backside.<br>
<br>
  Druid_1 casts spell "steam part 1" on Helpless_1<br>
<br>
Emote:   Helpless_1 is contained in the glimmer of frost.<br>
  System: 10 second "buff" symbol active on Helpless_1 now allowing "steam part 2" spell to land on him.<br>
<br>
  Wizz_1 casts "steam part 2" on Helpless_1<br>
<br>
Emote:  Helpless_1 is seared by the breath of the elements!<br>
  System:  10 second "buff" is now dispelled and Helpless_1 is hit for a 500pt DD and a 100 a click DoT, with fear component which lasts about 3 clicks.<br>
<br>
<br>
  So together the 2 managed to Scald the Mob, which sent him running in pain till the vapors subside.    Would be a VERY cool new system, and if it took too much coding, I am sure it wouldn't break their hearts to make an entire expansion just to release the stuff.<br>
<br>
    For melee, you could incorperate new attacks as well, where a caster imbues you with magics and you unleash a huge attack, or possibly (seems much harder to code though) the ability to use dual attacks with other characters (you autoattack on them maybe, and while locked in like that you are on /autofollow basically, and they hit 2.5 times as brutally)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
  Anyways, wanted to see if people thought this would be a cool idea, and if any of those admirers knew how to recomend things to VI somehow.    Would love to see such TACTICS incorperated, make your group choices much more crucial at least. ;) <p><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD>
